body:
**Kubernetes version**:

master branch.

**Environment**:

OSX.

**What happened**:

```
go test -v ./pkg/kubelet/dockertools
...
=== RUN   TestDeleteContainerRemoveDeadContainer
--- FAIL: TestDeleteContainerRemoveDeadContainer (0.00s)
	controller.go:158: missing call(s) to *testing.MockNetworkPlugin.TearDownPod(is anything, is anything, is anything)
	controller.go:165: aborting test due to missing call(s)
=== RUN   TestGarbageCollectNetworkTeardown
--- FAIL: TestGarbageCollectNetworkTeardown (0.00s)
	controller.go:158: missing call(s) to *testing.MockNetworkPlugin.TearDownPod(is anything, is anything, is equal to {docker 1867})
	controller.go:165: aborting test due to missing call(s)
=== RUN   TestGarbageCollectZeroMaxContainers
--- FAIL: TestGarbageCollectZeroMaxContainers (0.00s)
	controller.go:158: missing call(s) to *testing.MockNetworkPlugin.TearDownPod(is anything, is anything, is anything)
	controller.go:165: aborting test due to missing call(s)
=== RUN   TestGarbageCollectNoMaxPerPodContainerLimit
--- FAIL: TestGarbageCollectNoMaxPerPodContainerLimit (0.00s)

=== RUN   TestGarbageCollectNoMaxLimit

=== RUN   TestSyncPodWithRestartPolicy

E0220 21:50:34.209048   99748 docker_manager.go:1565] unable to access pod data from container: no pod information labels on Docker container
--- FAIL: TestSyncPodWithRestartPolicy (0.00s)
        Error Trace:    docker_test.go:50
			docker_manager_test.go:943
	Error:		Received unexpected error "expected []string{\"inspect_container\", \"inspect_container\", \"stop\"}, got []string{\"inspect_container\", \"stop\"}"

=== RUN   TestGetPodStatusNoSuchContainer
E0220 21:50:34.222198   99748 docker_manager.go:2702] Unable to inspect container "nosuchcontainer": Error: No such container: nosuchcontainer
E0220 21:50:34.222567   99748 docker_manager.go:1756] Can't make a ref to pod foo, container POD: 'selfLink was empty, can't make reference'

--- FAIL: TestGetPodStatusNoSuchContainer (0.00s)
        Error Trace:    docker_test.go:50
			docker_manager_test.go:1837
	Error:		Received unexpected error "expected []string{\"inspect_container\", \"create\", \"start\", \"inspect_container\", \"inspect_container\", \"create\", \"start\", \"inspect_container\"}, got []string{\"create\", \"start\", \"inspect_container\", \"inspect_container\", \"create\", \"start\", \"inspect_container\"}"

--- FAIL: TestSyncPodDeadInfraContainerTeardown (0.00s)

	controller.go:158: missing call(s) to *testing.MockNetworkPlugin.TearDownPod(is equal to new, is equal to foo, is anything)
	controller.go:165: aborting test due to missing call(s)
```

title: Dockertools unit test failed on OSX
